textBeforeTable: Finland Head Coach Henrik Dettmann: "Funny game, it was like the stockmarket, vibrating all way long. These two teams are very similar and tonight we had better luck." Hungary Head Coach Mészáros Lajos: "Congratulations to our opponents. We had a hard game with ups and downs. At the end we were unlucky. The audience was unbelievable. We have to win against Portugal at home and in Finland too." Quotes Hungary vs. Finland 12.08.2011 The top two sides at the end of the AQR will advance to the EuroBasket, which tips off on August 31. The next game in the AQR will be when Finland host Portugal on Monday. Horvath led a balanced Hungarian attack with 15 points. Veteran point guard Teemu Rannikko led the Finns with 16 points while Lee contributed 14 and Kimmo Muurinen 12. With the clock winding
